[[File:Archives du Maroc.jpg|thumb|right|Archives du Maroc, Rabat, 2016]]
The '''Archives du Maroc''' (est. 2007) is an [[archives]] in [[Rabat]], [[Morocco]], on Avenue Ibn Battouta. Jamaâ Baida became director in 2011.<ref>{{citation |title=Histoire: 55 ans après l'indépendance, le Maroc se dote d'Archives nationales |language=fr |work=[[20minutes.fr]] |date=26 January 2013 |url= http://www.20minutes.fr/monde/1087985-20130126-histoire-55-ans-apres-independance-maroc-dote-archives-nationales }}</ref> It opened to the public in 2013.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.lopinion.ma/def.asp?codelangue=23&id_info=33073 |language=fr |title= 'Archives du Maroc' ouvre ses portes au public |date= 16 June 2013 |work=[[L'Opinion]] |location=Rabat }}</ref> Among its holdings are materials related to the colonial [[French protectorate in Morocco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.archivesdumaroc.ma/page/presentation.html |title=Presentation |publisher=Archives du Maroc |location=Rabat |language=fr |accessdate= 12 August 2017 }}</ref> The newly created Conseil national des archives (National Council on Archives) is expected to coordinate its activities with the Archives du Maroc.<ref>{{citation |title=Création d'un Conseil national des archives |date= 28 July 2017 |language=fr |work={{illm|Médias 24|fr}} |location=Casablanca |url= https://www.medias24.com/MAROC/Quoi-de-neuf/175434-Creation-d-un-Conseil-national-des-archives.html }}</ref>

