{{multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=April 2012}} {{notability|Biographies|date=April 2012}} }}
'''Jorun Solheim''' (born 18 November 1944) is a Norwegian [[social anthropology|social anthropologist]] and [[women's studies]] academic, whose work is centered on gender, culture and modernity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kilden.forskningsradet.no/c17385/artikkel/vis.html?tid%3D18317%26within_tid%3D18092 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-04-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020133737/http://kilden.forskningsradet.no/c17385/artikkel/vis.html?tid=18317&within_tid=18092 |archivedate=2013-10-20 |df= }}</ref>
She was lecturer in social anthropology at the [[University of Oslo]] from 1971 to 1983, Researcher at the [[Work Research Institute]] from 1981 to 2001 and Professor at the Centre for Women's Studies at the [[University of Oslo]] from 1994 to 1999. She is currently Senior Researcher at the [[Norwegian Institute of Social Research]]. In 2007, she became editor-in-chief of [[Tidsskrift for kjønnsforskning]]. She has a [[mag.art.]] (i.e. PhD) degree in social anthropology from 1970.
==Works== *''Kjønn og modernitet'', 2007 *''Den usynlige hånd?'', 2002 *''Den åpne kroppen'', 1998
