[[File:Marjan Mashkour,june 2005.jpg|thumb|Marjan Mashkour, June 2005]]
'''Marjan Mashkour''' ({{lang-fa|مرجان مشکور}}) received her Ph.D. in [[zooarchaeology]] in [[Paris]] (2001) and is a member of [[CNRS]]. She is the first [[Persian people|Iranian]] to specialize in the field of zooarchaeology and has been engaged in many field and laboratory projects in [[Iran]] and the [[Near East]]. Her research interest is late [[Paleolithic]] fauna of the [[Zagros Mountains]] and the [[List of domesticated animals|domestication]] of the [[wild goat]] in Iran. She has edited a number of books on the zooarchaeology of Europe and the Near East. She is helping the [[National Museum of Iran]] to establish a center for zooarchaeology and was involved in the setting up of the [[Zagros Paleolithic Museum]].

== Thesis ==
PhD Thesis (2001, [[University of Paris 1 Pantheon-Sorbonne|University of Paris I-Sorbonne]]): ''"Chasse et élevage du Néolithique à l’Âge du Fer dans la plaine de Qazvin (Iran). Étude archéozoologique des sites de Zagheh, Qabrestan et Sagzabad"'', (''"Hunting and farming from the Neolithic to the Iron Age in the plain of Qazvin (Iran). Archaeozoological study sites Zagheh, and Qabrestan Sagzabad"'').

